name: Root
summary: The root network is a meta subnet with id 0. This network determines the proportion of the network's block emission to be distributed to each subnet network. This is currently set to 1 TAO for every block mined.  Like other subnetworks, the root network consists of a set of validators that set weights (W). These weights are then processed by Yuma Consensus to determine an emission vector (E). The difference is that the vector E has a length equal to the number of active subnetworks currently running on the chain and each e_i in E is the emission proportion that subnet i receives every block. The root network also doubles as the network senate. This senate is the top 12 keys on this network which have been granted veto power on proposals submitted by the triumvirate.

Contributors who provide the best trading signals receive the highest rewards, attracting skilled traders, data scientists, and machine learning teams to compete.

name: Pre-training LLMs
summary: Pre-Training is dedicated to the creation of SOTA pretrained foundation models, rewarding contributors for achieving top performance on selected open datasets. Functioning as a continuous benchmark, the models that excel in head-to-head loss comparisons on evaluation data receive the highest rewards. The subnet has successfully developed models with 700 million and 7 billion parameters that outperform industry-leading counterparts like GPT-2 Large and Falcon-7B.

name: Sturdy
summary: Sturdy is focused on the creation of autonomous DeFi yield optimizers. Contributors develop algorithms to allocate assets among a fixed set of strategies or 'pools' with varying interest rates to maximize yield.

name: Dippy Roleplay
summary: The Dippy Roleplay subnet on Bittensor aims to create the world's best open-source roleplay LLM by leveraging the collective efforts of the open-source community.

name: Horde
summary: Horde is a cloud platform dedicated to networkless GPU-equipped servers. It implements hardware classes to establish a free market that optimizes for cost-effectiveness over merely the strongest hardware.

name: Dataverse
summary: Dataverse is focused on distributed data scraping to create datasets for training and other applications. It directs contributors to specific data sources for scraping and incentivizes them to store the data, ensuring easy retrieval and accessibility.

name: TAO Hash
summary: The first and leading subnet for decentralizing PoW (proof-of-work) mining hashrate, rental and exchange. Validators receive hashrate in exchange for weights, and miners speculate on hashrate, hashprice, and Alpha emissions.

name: HashTensor
summary: HashTensor is a decentralized Bittensor subnet designed to track and validate mining activity across multiple proof-of-work blockchains. By introducing a model called Proof of Effective Work (PoEW), the system rewards miners not just for raw hashrate, but for performance, uptime, and reliability, allowing them to earn Alpha tokens based on their actual contribution.

name: 404—GEN
summary: Three Gen incentivizes the development of AI models for generating 3D digital assets and the creation of synthetic 3D model datasets.

name: Zeus
summary: The Zeus Subnet leverages advanced AI models within the Bittensor network to forecast environmental data. This platform is engineered on a decentralized, incentive-driven framework to enhance trustworthiness and stimulate continuous technological advancement. The datasource for this subnet consists of ERA5 reanalysis data from the Climate Data Store (CDS) of the European Union's Earth observation programme (Copernicus). This comprises the largest global environmental dataset to date, containing hourly measurements from 1940 until the present across a multitude of hundreds of variables. Validators can stream data from this data source in real-time, allowing miners to be queried on terrabytes of data.

name: Nineteen

name: BitAgent

name: Desearch

Designed for the Bittensor community and general internet users, Desearch delivers an unbiased and verifiable search experience. Through our API, developers and AI builders are empowered to integrate AI search capabilities into their products, with access to metadata from platforms like X, Reddit, Arxiv and general web search.

name: Nuance

name: OMEGA Labs

Contributors capture videos with metadata such as title, tags, and descriptions, obtain ImageBind embeddings for video, audio, and captions, and upload them, creating one of the largest open-source multimodal datasets.

name: Protein Folding

name: Storb

name: Coldint

name: Bettensor

name: Candles

name: It's AI

name: ReadyAI
summary: ReadyAI is focused on data structuring, incentivizing the transformation of unstructured data from sources like videos, podcasts, text, and images into structured formats suitable for training AI models.

name: BitMind
summary: BitMind is focused on detecting AI-generated media. Contributors are incentivized to create advanced models that can reliably differentiate between authentic and fabricated content.

name: LogicNet
summary: LogicNet focuses on developing open-source mathematics and detailed data analysis models.

name: Web Agents
summary: Web Agents Subnet leverages our Infinite Web Arena (IWA) benchmark to incentivize Bittensor miners to develop SOTA web agents.

name: Fine-Tuning
summary: Fine-Tuning is focused on the production of fine-tuned models. Contributors are rewarded based on their models' head-to-head scores, with evaluations based on a continuous stream of synthetic data generated by the top LLMs. The evaluation data setup helps reduce the potential of the benchmark being gamed.

name: DistributedTraining
summary: DistributedTraining is focused on training a single LLM in a distributed setting. Contributors are incentivized to provide compute, bandwidth, and low latency, using compute to train local models and bandwidth and latency to facilitate the averaging of model weights across participants.

name: EdgeMaxxing

By optimizing popular models for edge devices, the subnet aims to transform idle computing resources into valuable contributors to decentralized inference networks.

name: Sportstensor

name: Masa

name: Graphite
summary: Graphite focuses on graph problems, which involve optimizing algorithms to solve computational challenges, such as finding the shortest path, optimizing network flow, or determining optimal arrangements.

name: Score Vision
summary: Score Vision is a decentralised computer vision framework built on Bittensor that drastically reduces the cost and time required for complex video analysis.

name: SWE-Rizzo

Our focus is on creating robust, scalable tools for software engineering, powered by open-source large language models. These tools should benefit both Bittensor community and the broader software engineering ecosystem. To achieve this, our miners compete to develop the best SWE (software engineering) pipelines and we score their performance.

name: Neural3D
summary: The goal of this subnet is to provide end users (game developers, virtual production, etc.) a way to populate 3D worlds by quickly generating high quality 3D assets based on text prompts via web app, API or plugins for game engines (e.g Unreal Engine & Unity), while simultaneously building a massive open-source library of 3D assets that can be used amongst other things, for further model training.

name: NextPlace

Discover what your home is likely to sell for, identify housing trends in real estate markets across the United States, earn Tao by unleashing your own AI models in the subnet, and so much more.

name: Polaris
summary: Polaris is a Bittensor subnet designed as a decentralized GPU compute marketplace and management layer. Its primary goal is to connect miners who have spare GPU resources with the Bittensor network, enabling those GPUs to be used for AI tasks and other compute-intensive workloads in a trustless environment.

name: Synth
summary: Synth creates the world's most powerful Synthetic price data for DeFi, enabling a paradigm shift in how agents model and optimise for the future.

name: Compute Subnet

Users can rent these resources for computational tasks, such as machine learning, data analysis, and more. The system ensures fair compensation for miners based on the quality and performance of their GPUs.

name: Tensorplex Dojo
summary: Tensorplex Dojo Subnet is an open platform designed to crowdsource high-quality human-generated datasets. Powered by Bittensor, the Dojo Subnet addresses these challenges by allowing anyone to earn TAO by labeling data or providing human-preference data. This approach democratizes the collection of human preference data, addressing existing equity issues and paving the way for more inclusive and ethical AI development.

name: Efficient Frontier

This project will leverage Bittensor's innovative blockchain-powered AI learning protocol to advance our journey in discovering optimal crypto trading strategies. Furthermore, through the use of SignalPlus' market-leading platform, every day users will now be equipped with a professional trading toolkit that is available right on their desktop, enabling true democratised access and empowering the open-access initiative.

As the project grows, Bitsec will expand coverage to other types of codebases.

For the first time, sophisticated attackers can be rewarded for their ingenuity through a powerful incentive mechanism designed to uncover vulnerabilities and build more resilient systems.

Our vision is to create the world’s most trusted source for news and fact verification, ensuring every user can rely on timely and accurate insights with help and power of decentralized AI community.

name: Merit

Machine vision technology has long proven effective in early diagnosis, which is crucial for curing cancer. Yet, until now, it has largely remained in the realm of whitepapers. SAFESCAN is a project dedicated to aggregating and enhancing the best algorithms for detecting various types of cancer and providing free computational power for practical cancer detection. We aim to create open-source products that support cancer diagnosis for both patients and doctors.
